data.name: rbIndividualAngle.ToolTip
data.value: If this is checked, all labels will be rotated indidually. Angle must be defined in any column of Attributes table.

data.name: rbCommonAngle.ToolTip
data.value: If this is checked, all labels will be rotated on the same angle.

data.name: chkPrioritizeLow.ToolTip
data.value: If this is checked, low values will be placed first with collision prevention, or on top otherwise.

data.name: chkPreventCollision.ToolTip
data.value: If this is not checked, high priority labels will be drawn over low priority labels. If it is checked only the higher priority label of two overlapping labels will be placed.

data.name: cmbPriorityField.ToolTip
data.value: By default, the FID is used to prioritize labels. This allows values from a field to be used instead.

data.name: lblHelp.Text
data.value: Each symbol group can have many members. Use the Members page to add or remove members manually, or based on a field characteristics. If no members appear in the Ungrouped list, you should first remove the labels from an existing group.
